  "couName": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The governing submission requirement (FDA-SUB-2024-001) mandates demonstration of model credibility at Medium risk level for Class II spinal implant devices; this requirement is documented in the package but is not formally linked via bindsRequirement per the Minimal profile binding rules.",
